    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-10-04T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-10-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="724"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.841/294: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodge</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-04T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1926—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Telegraph Department regarding tonnage duties, if any, assessed in Danish
                    ports. If duties are assessed state whether they are uniform and if not what
                    rates are assessed against American vessels as compared with rates assessed
                    against other foreign vessels, and Danish vessels. This information desired in
                    consideration of the contention of the Danish Government that in view of Article
                    I of the Treaty with Denmark of 1826, Danish vessels arriving in the United
                    States from Danish ports should be accorded the benefit of the minimum tonnage
                    duty of two cents per ton provided for in the Federal Statutes, which has been
                    accorded Norwegian vessels from Norwegian ports under the provisions of Article
                    8 of the Treaty with Norway of 1827.<note n="15" xml:id="d724fn15">Miller, <hi
                            rend="italic">Treaties</hi>, vol. 3, pp. 283, 288.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
